# Player Events

## Join Event
```java
@EventHandler
public void onJoin(PlayerJoinEvent event) {
    event.getPlayer().sendMessage("Hello " + event.getPlayer().getName());
}
```

## Quit Event
```java
@EventHandler
public void onQuit(PlayerQuitEvent event) {
    System.out.println(event.getPlayer().getName() + " left");
}
```

## Logic
- Player triggers event
- Event object stores data
- You read and modify behavior

## Edge Case
Null checks rarely needed here, but always assume player exists only during event.

# Block Events

## Block Break Example
```java
@EventHandler
public void onBreak(BlockBreakEvent event) {
    event.getPlayer().sendMessage("You broke " + event.getBlock().getType());
}
```

## Cancel Example
```java
@EventHandler
public void onBreak(BlockBreakEvent event) {
    if (event.getBlock().getType().toString().contains("DIAMOND")) {
        event.setCancelled(true);
    }
}
```

## Logic
- Event fires
- Check conditions
- Cancel or modify

## Testing
Try breaking diamond ore — should fail.

# Chat Events

## Example
```java
@EventHandler
public void onChat(AsyncPlayerChatEvent event) {
    event.setMessage("[Modified] " + event.getMessage());
}
```

## Logic
- Async event (runs off main thread)
- Modify message

## Warning
Avoid heavy tasks in async events.
